page.title: 06Fleetwood golf course
page.content: Situated to the south west of Fleetwood between Princes Way and the sea wall, a promenade. Approximately 1 mile long, a third of a mile wide at its widest point. The land is owned by Fleetwood Corporation, rented by the golf club. The club was founded in 1933. The club house is situated on Princes Way at the mid point of the golf course. It was previously farm land. There are 378 full members at the moment. There is evidence of a large rubbish tip at the north end. Other recreational pursuits in the clubhouse are snooker and playing cards. There is one small pond (30 yards across) at the north end of the course
